<Content>Love ,love, love it!!! This hotel is amazing. We stayed here with friends for our New Year getaway and we were all very impressed. Deco, rooms, bar and staff all very clean and contemporary and the atmosphere is fab. We spent the afternoon supping cocktails, (expensive, but what isn't in London?) which were supplied by a lovely, very chatty and charming waitress. However, be warned, we were quite happy to go to the bar to be served and if we had have done, we would have saved ourselves 拢15 on her service charge, (we were unaware we would be charged extra just for drinks)! The hotel is quite a trek from the tourist areas of London but the tube is only a two minute walk away. However, there are loads of cool bars and restaurants in Shoreditch so next time we would probably stay local. The hotel also does a great unbiased review leaflet which can be picked up from your room- definitely worth a look!Overall, we all thoroughly enjoyed our stay, we loved the healthy breakfast too- left in a small paper bag on our door handle! A yummy yoghurt, fresh orange juice and a banana (a great healthy hangover cure!!!!). Can't wait for our next visit! 
