<Content>The best hotel I've stayed at - anywhere! The Hoxton is, in my opinion, the best hotel I鈥檝e ever stayed in! A combination of getting a fantastic price from Superbreak, coupled with a quirky, innovative non-pretentious but very fab hotel made this birthday trip one to remember! The hotel is situated a few minutes walk from Old Street Station and doesn鈥檛 look that interesting from the outside. However, on entering the lobby, you are transported into a mad mix of Scottish baronial, ultra modern and quite a bit kitsch! Giant papier mache eagles in varying states of flight soar above head (sounds tacky but isn鈥檛!) and you鈥檙e surrounded by a variety of comfy sofas and designer chairs at either end of the lobby with a roaring fire on each end to top it all off. The reception staff were efficient and friendly and we were checked in quickly. On stepping out of the lift and turning the corner, you enter the corridors of rooms 鈥?lit with funky floor to ceiling orange lights (I think were a sophisticated in/out indicator!). The room wasn鈥檛 massive, but certainly not tiny either. A really lovely bed with trendy paper, scissors, stone cushions and a chaise longue and a built in desk/mirror/tv unit. The bathroom was clean and really modern with big shower and a retro touch in the form of Pears soap! Another nice touch was that the middle of the mirror is heated so when the bathroom steams up after a shower, you can still see!The best bit (other than the price/design/staff!) was the added value elements. Breakfast is included with Superbreak and comes in the form of a brown paper bag hung outside your door with a banana, a fruit and granola yogurt and a Pret orange juice. Something different and refreshing. There is a fridge in your room 鈥?with a free half pint of milk and free bottles of water too 鈥?can鈥檛 complain! You also get a little fold out credit card sized map telling you all about the cool things in the Shoreditch/Hoxton area which was great for finding places to eat and go out. Extras were the best value 鈥?50p for a can of coke at reception 鈥?same for a bar of chocolate - I think a beer was 拢1...! No rip offs here! Free broadband access in the lobby, pay per view movies were also cheap if I remember rightly and these little touches made the whole experience fantastic! I鈥檝e just booked to go back again in a few weeks!In terms of eating 鈥?Wapping Food is great for a special occasion and Zigfrid von Underbelly on Hoxton Square is fab for a reasonably priced casual meal.In short, I wouldn鈥檛 stay anywhere else! (Unless there was no room at the Hoxton!) 
