<Content>Perfect hotel and location We booked this hotel before it opened for business and therefore were lucky enough to get one of the 拢29 room offers.Now that we have stayed this weekend, we would have been happy to pay more and will most certainly return. This hotel is brand new and amazingly clean and stylish. Although it is obviously aimed at the 20 - 40 generation - black tiled bathrooms, dark moody coloured walls, steel lined rather cell like corridors - the crisp white Egyption cotton bedding and deep piled white towels gave a real feeling of luxury (and we are in our 50s!!). The tea tray contained real coffee sachets and the fridge had complimentary water and fresh milk - a lovely touch. The bathroom was large and the power shower amazing. The reception staff were extrememly friendly and welcoming. The noise from the lively bar and grille downstairs did not infiltrate at all to our room on the 3rd floor and facing the back of the hotel. The sound proofing must have been very good, as we heard no noise from other rooms or the corridor all night. The King size double bed was SO comfortable too. This hotel really is offering superb quality accommodation at a truely budget price. Even the Pret a Manger breakfast hanging on our door the next morning was fresh, chilled, healthy and tasty. We ate the evening before at a lovely Vietnamese cafe just round the corner in Old Street and not far away is the trendy Hoxton Square with White Cube Gallery and some lovely bars. The hotel itself is only a 5 minute walk from Old Stree tube, which itself is only 2 stops from Kings Cross Station, so a brilliant location. We visited the lovely intimate Almeida Theatre in Upper Street (Angel tube - one stop) on the Saturday night. All in all a wonderful weekend and a highly recommended hotel. We will definately return. 
