<Content>Great hotel, but they need to ask Islington Council to fix loose road access!! Arrived via Tube at Old Street Station - take exit 6 and walk straight on for 3-5 minutes, and the hotel is on the right. The area itself is not really very nice - this is not the sort of place you want to bring your mom and grandmother for a touristy break. This is for young people who want to party, City-visitors, or people like me who just hate touristy areas and prefer to stay in someplace a bit more out-of-the-way but still close enough to the action to get there easily.Check in was fine, very friendly clerk who sold us a can of Coke for 50p before sending us up to connecting rooms. Both rooms were very clean with extremely comfy beds, bathrooms were excellent and the fridge with the free bottles of water and milk were fab. TV was very nice flat-screen, but could do with adding a few more channels on offer (just BBC1, BBC2, ITV, channel 5, Sky News, Bloomberg, and Discovery). The breakfast that comes with the room was very nice (OJ, banana and yoghurt). I cannot fault the rooms in any way.The hotel bar was full of pretty people, which was fine as I'm not ugly. However, the bar staff were dismal and slow - they seemed quite inexperienced and I waited 5 minutes to order when they weren't even very busy. I think their long list of specialty cocktails makes their jobs slower, and the chap in front of me seemed to be reading the recipe out of a book. Not very impressive.There are only two things about this place that bugged me. First - there is a loose road access in the second lane of the street at the front of the hotel which makes a horrible noise when lorries drive over it. Islington Council really needs to be contacted about it and it needs to be fixed - after our first restless night we went to Tesco and bought earplugs, and were able to sleep after that. However, when you're not used to sleeping by a busy road that noise can really make your night unbearable.Secondly, we requested a cab to take us from the hotel to Victoria on a Sunday morning. One of the clerks at the desk booked us a car, which turned out to be a rather nasty minicab. We had a lot of luggage (10 days shopping in London and Paris will result in such things) and the guy hadn't even cleaned out the boot - we had real trouble getting the luggage in the back and kept some of it on our laps. He then tried to convice us to let him take us all the way to Gatwick, but there was no way we were going to put up with THAT. So, if you find a driver you really like during your stay and you need to book a car (as you need to do on Sunday mornings), get a card yourself or take a number down off the side of a cab. That was really disappointing.All in all, though, very nice and I have booked another stay for December already. 
