<Content>2nd Stay - Much Better! I returned to the Hoxton for a 2nd stay, and I'd like to pass on my advice for the best stay possible at this hotel.Firstly, you don't need to hand over your credit card if you think you'll not incur expenses during your stay.Secondly, to avoid noise, ask for a room at the back, not over looking grt eastern street, and not overlooking the atrium as both these locations are very noisy. I got a room overlooking willow st at the back of the hotel - this is an access road and rarely used by traffic. Unlike my previous visit where I had a sleepless stay, I had a restful one this time!Thirdly, its not well advertised, but if you don't have a laptop, ask at reception to use their free internet faciilities in their conference room. They have around 5 pc's in there for guests to use free of use, unlimited time !I still like the rooms and because it's new the hotel does have nice fixtures and fittings, but on close inspection these aren't quality, and will soon fade i fear... so book in whilst everything is still fresh.Also, I agree with previous customers about the corriders, they're trying to be industrial and funky, but in reality are very dark, and also quite disorienting.If you want a hip hotel, well out of the tourist area for a good price - go for it and take advantage of the prices on their website. 
